            <title>[SPARK-16018] Shade netty for shuffle to work on YARN</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-16018</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We replaced LazyFileRegion with netty&apos;s DefaultFileRegion. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because of this (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-15178&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-15178&lt;/a&gt;), we have a dependency on netty&#8194;4.0.25.Final or &amp;gt;, but hadoop is on 4.0.23.Final, so the shuffle jar won&apos;t load in nodemanager as its trying to find a new version of the class. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to shade netty&apos;s classes inorder to load the latest version we need and not depend on the one loaded by hadoop.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
